[SHORT DESC]
Always leaves the foe with at least 1 HP.

[LONG DESC]
<h2>Description</h2>
<p>Deals damage. If the move would cause enough damage to the opponent to faint it will always leave the opponent with 1 HP instead, regardless of how much damage would have been inflicted.</p>

<h2>Competitive Use</h2>
<p>False Swipe has no competitive use in singles. In doubles and triples it can be used to reduce a teammate to 1 HP safely in order to bring the Base Power of Flail or Reversal to 200.</p>

<h2>Related Moves</h2>
<p><a href="/bw/moves/return">Return</a> is a much stronger alternative with no drawbacks.</p>
<p><a href="/bw/moves/double-edge">Double-Edge</a> is an even stronger alternative that inflicts recoil on the user.</p>